    "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nWhen writing empty data into Parquet, the metadata does not exist.\r\n\r\n**Steps/Code to reproduce bug**\r\n```\r\n=== create empty parquet=== \r\nfrom pyspark.sql.types import *\r\nschema = StructType([\r\n  StructField(\"c1\", StringType()),\r\n  StructField(\"c2\", IntegerType()),\r\n  StructField(\"c3\", IntegerType()),\r\n])\r\ndata = []\r\ndf = spark.createDataFrame(\r\n        SparkContext.getOrCreate().parallelize(data, numSlices=2),\r\n        schema)\r\ndf.write.parquet(\"/tmp/a\")\r\nspark.read.parquet(\"/tmp/a\").show()\r\n+---+---+---+\r\n| c1| c2| c3|\r\n+---+---+---+\r\n+---+---+---+\r\n\r\n=== write on GPU===\r\nwith_gpu_session(lambda spark: spark.read.parquet(\"/tmp/a\")\r\n  .write.mode(\"overwrite\").partitionBy('c1', 'c2').parquet(\"/tmp/new-a\"))\r\n\r\nls /tmp/new-a\r\n// has no data files\r\n\r\n=== read on GPU ===\r\nspark.read.parquet(\"/tmp/new-a\").show()\r\n// error occurs\r\npyspark.sql.utils.AnalysisException: Unable to infer schema for Parquet. It must be specified manually.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nCheck Parquet, Orc and other formats when writing empty data.\r\n",
